description: N.B. Star Trek: The Next Generation features in a text article about the show. There is no comic strip for same in this issue, and none of the characters appearing on the cover should be added to this title's character list, as they do not appear within.

In the 23rd century, Don grew up in one of the last small towns on earth. Like the millions of other residents, his eyes were glued to the sky when the promise of a better life launched in the form of a state-of-the-art rocket ship. As he grows up, Don's dreams of space flight gets pushed to the background and become all but forgotten when he meets the girls of dreams. Together they start a cozy life and start planning a family. Everything is going wonderfully until Don sees a chance, and must choose between the life he has and the life he always dreamed of.

The noise of thunder, part fifteen.

Tessa's powers are back! The red-haired can't wait to use them against the Artisan, but the mysterious genius behind Luna is resourceful and determined to use Tessa, Jill and the cosmic event called "Resonance" to reach Manifest. Meanwhile, Thunder Girl meets Dawnchild's grandmother, Blind Sparrow: does she really know how to reach Tessa?
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part Fifteen

description:
The lost years, part one.

Despite the friendship between Tessa and Dawnchild, the Nayan people and their leader, Blind Sparrow, look at Thunder Girl with great concern. The reason lies in the past, when Tessa Theus was just a teenager.
name: The Lost Years, Part One

description: College life ain't easy, especially when you're different, and folks around you wonder how you got there. Getting by is tough enough as it is, dealing with body changes, romantic interests, peer pressure, class work, and public image. The human condition spares no one in this world, not even robots. Featuring a backup short story illustrated by Seth T Hahne.

Being a robot doesn't make dating any easier. Carb and Gracie head out for a night on the town, but whatever is going on inside Carb's head gets in the way. Typical human condition. Featuring a backup short story illustrated by Sabrina Scott.

This third issue of the free Caliber Rounds "magazine" is a special issue that spotlights four of our comic book writers and the thought process in developing their respective series. Continuing the spotlighting of Caliber's creators and titles, this issue also features the continuation of Caliber's history, a look at some numbers of Caliber, Tony Meillo's Gapo the Clown new strip, and a special bonus of the Zombie Dawn comic that serves as a prequel to the cult classic movie.

Issue Four of the free Caliber Rounds "magazine" features a preview of titles released in the Fall of 2015. Taking a look at such titles as Bayani and The Nine Daughters of the Moon, Killing Castro, The SixSmiths, Boy Zero, and The God Child. In addition, an all-new Gapo the Clown strip and publisher Gary Reed continues his "History of Caliber Comics". Concluding with part two of the Zombie Dawn movie prequel comic for fans to enjoy.

Caliber Rounds #5 presents an inside look at Caliber's anthologies with a focus on two horror anthologies, Danny Boyd's Chillers and E. Mayem Briem's Horror City. Chillers are all new stories centered around the theme of the Chillers feature film movie released by legendary Troma Films. While Horror City features gripping short stories from a team of international artists and writers. Both feature a complete story in this issue as a bonus. Plus, a look at other anthologies such as Night Pieces and Midnight Mortuary and a glance at the upcoming Calibrations publication. And finally a look at The History of Caliber Comics continues.

This issue of Caliber Rounds takes a look at the long running series, Saint Germaine. A figure shrouded in history, this is Gary Reeds take on the mysterious immortal. In addition to a look at the storylines of the series illustrated by Vince Locke and Andy Bennett and guest stars, there is a bonus story on Saint Germaine. Also included is a look at Gary Scott Beattys uniquely illustrated Jazz series and at the all new version of Caliber Presents. Plus regular features such as Gapo the Clown and a History of Caliber.

In this FREE Special Summer Preview issue we take a look at some of Caliber Comics upcoming titles. Covered within are preview pages, interviews, and more information with looks at: Squalor, Untouchables, Disciples, P.I. Jane, Salt, and Amongst the Stars. Plus a bonus story of the prelude leading into the Inferno graphic novel by Mike Carey (Lucifer) and Michael Gaydos (Jessica Jones); and the continuation of the History of Caliber from publisher Gary Reed.

Escape

With the help of an addict, Dr. Wagner escapes from the cartel.
name: Escape

description:
Waiting

The cartel searches for Dr. Wagner who is waiting for nightfall to attempt to leave the city and make his way home.
name: Waiting

description:
Into the Furnace

Dr. Wagner makes his way deeper into the city, to a place called "The Furnace" to find what he needs for his plan to escape the city.
name: Into the Furnace

description: Adriana, Samson's wife, is dead. A very very upset Samson just wants to be left alone. But there are some individuals that want to meet him. And they are very old...and they are very hungry...

Twenty years ago, Nuclear and biological warfare ravaged the planet. Now, a sheltered group of humans are forced into the outside world to face the reality of their new lives and the mutated humans who now roam the surface.

Twenty years ago, Nuclear and biological warfare ravaged the planet. Now, a sheltered group of humans are forced into the outside world to face the reality of their new lives and the mutated humans who now roam the surface.

Join Mal, Evie, Carlos, Jay, Ben and all-new characters as their stories unfold in Disney Descendants Wicked World Wish Granted animated shorts. There's no shortage of magic, mystery, and mischief at Auradon Prep. Princess Audrey, daughter of Princess Aurora, opts for a new hairdoor don't? Mal conjures some unforeseen trouble while cheering at Spirit Day. Jordan, The Genie's daughter, gets some unexpected company at her magic lamp, and more! Fans of the hit Disney Channel original movie Disney Descendants will love the graphic novel adaptation of the Wicked World Wish Granted shorts from Joe Books.
name: Wish Granted

description: Writer and creator E. Mayen Briem is joined by a collection of artistic talents such as Denis Vermesse, Alessio Mariani, Matrino Resendez, and Loki Yarison in spinning new tales of horror for fans worldwide. This issue contains three horrific looks with Point Zero, Zombies House of Pleasure, and Rotten Neighborhood.

Continuing the horror anthology with independent stories comprising the tapestry of the tale of Payne City, a deranged place of murder and terror. In this issue, Blood X Blood with art from Alvaro Murga and Jorge Humberto Diaz, spins a tale of human sacrifice and Perfect Victim tells of a desperate attempt of a young girl to be different than dozens of previous victims. Illustrated by Heather Uebel. Yair P.T. finishes off this issue with a short of Mr. Clone Goes to Washington. All stories written by series creator, E. Mayen Briem.

In "Johnny Saturn: Intelligent Redesign" part I, the Siege of Squadron Premiere Plaza is over, and now it's time to bury the dead and assess the future. For

Johnny Saturn, the questions keep coming-what is his relationship with the Squadron Premiere? Has his mental health become an issue, or is it still an asset he can take advantage of? The answers aren't easy, and Spire City and its heroes hang in the balance! This issues features murders, funerals, corporate takeovers, and the beginning of a false flag operation that will upset the world's balance of power.

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 24 pages of comics, three characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, six bonus sketchbook pages, and part one of the serialized prose story "Death on the Docks," all for 40 total pages of content!
name: Intelligent Redesign I

description:
As Johnny Saturn's mind fractures and the Utopian is powerless, Tactical makes his greatest stab at vengeance yet! Don't miss Tara 5.0, the android scorned! And, Wissenschaft's delusions come to reveal a frighteningly real threat that could set the planet afire! The temperature rises in this red-hot issue of Johnny Saturn, "Intelligent Redesign II."

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 24 pages of comics, two characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, six bonus sketchbook pages, and part two of the serialized prose story "Death on the Docks," all for 39 total pages of content!
name: Intelligent Redesign II

description:
At last, In "Johnny Saturn: Intelligent Redesign" part III, Johnny Saturn II prepares to make the ultimate sacrifice, and he and Dr. Wissenschaft face-off in deadly combat. Who lives, who dies? This is no rhetorical question, because one of them does die, and Greg Buchanan faces down his mortality with a manic laugh. Look up into the sky as antique terrors descend from the mists of time to rain down destruction on Spire City.

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 22 pages of comics, two characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, six bonus sketchbook pages, and part three of the serialized prose story "Death on the Docks," all for 37 total pages of content!
name: Intelligent Redesign III

description:
"Johnny Saturn: Intelligent Redesign" part IV is where Thu-Lynn's monstrous plan for Spire City is at last revealed, and it's her champion Dark Requiem vs. his former teammates, the Squadron Premiere! Eris, goddess of discord, wants in on the action, and she is not to be denied. Witness a super showdown of epic proportions when it's Dark Requiem vs. the world.

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 24 pages of comics, one characters' Who's Who page, one Spire City map, six bonus sketchbook pages, and part four of the serialized prose story "Death on the Docks," all for 38 total pages of content!
name: Intelligent Redesign IV

description:
Johnny Saturn: Intelligent Redesign" part V, Dark Requiem's and Thu-Lynn's tragic love affair crashes to its cataclysmic end, but what happens is a testament to loyalty that you will not forget. In addition, Tara and Mollie finally come face to face, the Utopian makes a series of decisions that change his life (and Spire City) forever, and Team Saturn is born out of darkest necessity.

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 26 pages of comics, two characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, six bonus sketchbook pages, and part five of the serialized prose story "Death on the Docks," all for 40 total pages of content!
name: Intelligent Redesign V

description:
"Johnny Saturn: Intelligent Redesign" part VI: This is it-Johnny Saturn vs. Dr. Wissenschaft, and only one will emerge alive! This battle has been brewing since issue 1, and now it ends decisively. This issue is marked with a betrayal that will shock you, alliances that will confound you, and an ending that turns well-known plot lines on their heads. This is a giant-sized issue, with 36 pages of comic, not the standard 24.

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 36 pages of comics, three characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, six bonus sketchbook pages, and the conclusion of the serialized prose story "Death on the Docks," all for 56 total pages of content!
name: Intelligent Redesign VI

description:
We learned in Like Father, Like Daughter #1 that this is the story about a teenage girl (Casey) whose father left her at a young age to become a full time superhero (Invulnerable). She has to deal with seeing her father everywhere and the world loving him while she views him in his true colors; as a man who abandoned his true responsibilities as a parent!

We also learned in the debut issue of "Like Father, Like Daughter", that Casey has now developed some of the same super human powers that her father has.

How will Casey deal with her new found powers? And more importantly, how will this affect her social life?
Casey heroically intervenes in a dangerous situation involving school bullying then comes face to face with her father Invulnerable for the first time in 10 years!

Brick hits the fan as the little-used United States Military gets involved in the fight to stop the Rock-pocalypse! But is 94% of the U.S. GDP enough to stop the rocks? Find out in the special double-sized Volume 3!
Find out the origin of rock ass-kicker Buck Stone in Volume 4 of the indie book that Enron dubbed "too big to fail"

No one at the rehab clinic believed Buck Stone when he proclaimed that the rocks would attack. Now they're all dead (most of them died due to nose bleeds and affluenza, but you get the point). Ever since the rock invasion, Buck has dedicated himself to saving humanity and restoring the planet of its honest politicians and benevolent dictators. Fortunately, through his years of preparing for the rock-pocalypse at the local sperm bank, Buck discovered the one mystic who knows how to stop the rocks. Who could it be? The answer is in Volume 5... or not. I can't remember, my brain function is so low, I'm not even legally considered "alive."

Voyage... to the Earth!

From prehistoric Mars to its exploration of space, witness how Mars mythologized its sister planet, Earth. Ever wonder what an alien planet's science fiction would look like? This issue offers a new sci-fi masterpiece in comics form.
name: Voyage... to the Earth!

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a bi-weekly series featuring some of the greatest Marvel characters. Lady Mastermind and Dark Beast complete the X-Men set, with Miles Morales Spider-Man launching an all-new Amazing Spider-Man collection.
name: Silk [White Bishop]

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a bi-weekly series featuring some of the greatest Marvel characters. Lady Mastermind and Dark Beast complete the X-Men set, with Miles Morales Spider-Man launching an all-new Amazing Spider-Man collection.
name: Spider-Man Noir [White Pawn]

description: Artist Herb Trimpe is joined by writer Steve Englehart for another Hulk-sized Marvel Masterworks edition! But first, a trip to Counter-Earth, where Hulk confronts his most-hated enemy: Bruce Banner! Add in the Rhino and the Abomination, and the action and drama can't be contained! Then, Hulk heads for Canada where the X-Men's Mimic returns, and the Wendigo makes his first appearance! And Hulk's travels will take him both over land and undersea until he returns to the United States to unleash his vengeance on General Thunderbolt Ross! When the malevolent M.O.D.O.K. mutates Betty Ross into the Harpy, Hulk must save her - even if she's now married to Glenn Talbot - in an adventure that ends like every Hulk story ought to: with the green goliath battling giant monsters! Collecting INCREDIBLE HULK (1968) #157-170.
name: Volume 9

description: The Hulk is out for revenge! And he'll have plenty of heavy hitters to unleash his anger on in the latest Marvel Masterworks! The Abomination, Juggernaut and Rhino are just the first in a murderer's row of earthshaking enemies before the ever-Incredible Hulk. Then, a battle with the Cobalt Man will send Hulk raging to Attilan, home of the Inhumans! To save their hidden city, they launch Hulk into deep space - but a mean green course correction lands Hulk on Counter-Earth! There, he and Adam Warlock must save the other Earth before an express rocket home lands the Hulk in the Canadian wild, where he'll battle the Wendigo - and in one of the most important stories in Marvel history, face off against Wolverine in the X-Man-to-be's first appearance! Collecting INCREDIBLE HULK (1968) #171-183.
name: Volume 10

description:
Part 2: Breakout

A.D.S. Agent Wen, codename Orchid, was sent by her boss to infiltrate A.S. Industries. They hope to find evidence that links Alvin Severnya, C.E.O. of A.S. Industries to illegal activities. Orchid infiltrates the compound undercover as Fujiko Simmons, who is the personal assistant of Alvin Severnya and currently on vacation. She manages to get the files needed for the investigation but runs into problems when the real Fujiko returns from her vacation unexpectedly and stirs up some trouble at the front desk...
name: Part 2: Breakout

description:
Part 3: Survival

A.D.S. agent Wen, codename Orchid, was sent by her boss to infiltrate A.S. Industries. They hope to find evidence that links Alvin Severnya, C.E.O. of A.S. Industries to illegal activities. However during the operation, Orchid was captured, stripped of her clothes and tied up in an old warehouse. Ever resourceful, she managed to escape however and make her way to the top of the building in hopes to get her bearings. Unfortunately for her though, she was no longer in New York City but New Jersey - and naked!
name: Part 3: Survival

description:
Join the Fight Part 4

As romance sparks between Danielle and Miguel, the powers of the Protectors begin to manifest themselves in surprising ways. But it might already be too late, as the Dissenters attack Chicago.
name: Join the Fight Part 4

description:
Join the Fight Part 5

War rages in the skies over Chicago, as the Protectors take the battle to the flagship of the Dissenter fleet. How can the Protectors possibly triumph against overwhelming odds?
name: Join the Fight Part 5

description:
Choose

The band is split and cast to the winds. Luke begins a quest to find his lost and pregnant love, Kenji struggles to hold the camp together, and Donna and Raina travel the world in search of help. The mysterious power is at last unlocked, and the Veratu confronts Donna with a fateful choice that could change everything. Death, life, and rock and roll in the penultimate chapter of the Rainbow in the Dark saga!
name: Choose

description:
End

The band is split and cast to the winds. Luke begins a quest to find his lost and pregnant love, Kenji struggles to hold the camp together, and Donna and Raina travel the world in search of help. The mysterious power is at last unlocked, and the Veratu confronts Donna with a fateful choice that could change everything. Death, life, and rock and roll in the penultimate chapter of the Rainbow in the Dark saga!
name: End

description:
Crime Takes a Holiday

Two complete stories! In "Crime Takes a Holiday," Rob's vacation to the French Riviera is interrupted when he learns that a longtime nemesis is operating in the area. Then, in "Not Your Father's Private Eye," Rob becomes the subject of a feature story about modern private security services.
name: Crime Takes a Holiday

description:
Sky High

Jara Bint Rih got injured during World War 3 and spent the last three years of her life in search of a suit she hoped would restore her ability to walk. She and her best friend Lucia Mason found the suit when they were attacked by a gang. But Jara managed to fend the gang off by using the suit. Now, as Shade, she fights to bring down Meta Systems, a multi-billion dollar corporation doing human experiments and building war machines and its boss, the one responsible for her injury in the first place: Ashley Simmons.
name: Sky High

description: Scotland's twisted anthology title returns with a third issue that is resolutely old-school in design and modern in approach. Behind its fearsome cover lurks four tales of terror, each with its own unique style. This issue presents an atmospheric adaptation of Edgar Allan Poe's The Raven.

Revealing the Wounded

The Kalizarians race to bring the Seal back to their homeland but their journey is far from over as Ravenwood and his group chase them every step of the way. Back at the Garrison, Raulph and Eva tend to an ailing Silvermain while Cromwell and Gorden overlook the destructive aftermath of the Rats' exodus from the city. Meanwhile, the remaining Kalizarians find trouble in their own ranks as Molock's apprentice joins them brewing plans of his own.
name: Revealing the Wounded

description:
Tracking the Dogged

Winter is upon the land bringing nothing but despair. The Seal is lost once again with a weary Ravenwood wondering how much more of this he can take and a nervous Pete regretting his decision to join them. At the mansion, Silvermain, Raulph and Eva begin their efforts to thwart the coming assassination attempt on Christian, yet the boy is strangely less than concerned. But in the city another assassination proves more successful as the first phase of the Earl's plan takes shape - the death of Cromwell.
name: Tracking the Dogged

description:
Tracking the Dogged Part Two

As Cromwell recovers from an assasination attempt, Prince Christian's personal guard finally joins them at the Earl Hadge's mansion but it's unsure whether the prince is any safer as the plot against him moves onward.

Meanwhile, Ravenwood and the remainder of the group pursue the rats, ever closer to their goal of recovering the Seal.
name: Tracking the Dogged Part Two

description:
Devils at the Gate

Molock is finally in possession of the Seal, but not without Ravenwood and his group ready to make a final siege on the Kalizarian keep.
name: Devils at the Gate

description:
Catching the Devil

The battle for the Seal begins as Ravenwood and his group stage a last stand against Molock.

Silvermain helps thwart Prince Christian's assassination, only to come across a conspiracy ready to envelope everyone in it's path.

And as plague makes it way through the city, the Kalizarian Ellision decides to add his own brand of the dark arts into the mix.
name: Catching the Devil

description:
The Devil in Your Home

With Ravenwood, Pandora, and Klea captured by the Kalizarians, it's all up to Gabriel and Pete to rescue them and capture the Seal once and for all.
name: The Devil in Your Home

description:
Treasure Hard Fought

Ravenwood, Pandora, and Klea face the final battle for the Seal but the war is far from over as plague ravages Earl Hadge's city.
name: Treasure Hard Fought

description:
In the Ending We Start

The final issue of the Thieves' Quest storyline! The Seal is back and safe at Hulux's manor. The battle was won but the war is far from over as Silvermain and Raulph are still trapped in Earl Hadge's plague ravaged city, now facing a full on assault by the Kalizarians.
name: In the Ending We Start

description:
THE DOLL Part One.

Will Saunders, a well-known businessman, returns to Terminus after a long absence. The motives behind his departure remain a mystery, not only for the influential residents of the city, but also for his closest friends. What has so suddenly changed Saunders' life and what will the consequences be? The first episode of the 9-part story inspired by one of the best novels of all times. Great jumping-on point for new readers!
name: The Doll Part 1 of 9

description:
THE DOLL Part Two.

While Will Saunders is slowly getting used to life after returning to Terminus, let's take a look into the diary of his old friend, Atticus Vordin, so that we may learn the secrets of his dark past.
name: The Doll Part 2 of 9

description: A modern-day Wendy Darling confronts her sanity when she suspects a mysterious flying boy has abducted her little brother. Placed in a new school, Wendy struggles to separate fantasy from reality as those around her start to resemble characters from Neverland.

A modern-day Wendy Darling confronts her sanity when she suspects a mysterious flying boy has abducted her little brother. Placed in a new school, Wendy struggles to separate fantasy from reality as those around her start to resemble characters from Neverland.
The story continues!

With Christopher Quin now a happily married man, will he jump head first in to domestic euphoria or will the call to heroism be too much for him to resist?

WHATEVER HAPPENED TO THE ARCHETYPE?
With the death rattles creeping ever closer and the black cloud of desperation tapping him on the shoulder, Christopher Quin has one last chance to convince his mystery visitor the truth.

Which Man is He?

In the Book 1 Finale, Rowen finally catches a break and discovers the secret of the goblin's demise. But he isn't alone in this, as he finds himself assisting the Grayven Guard.

When word of his existence gets back to the authorities, Rowen discovers the consequences of making his quest public, and is given a new name.
name: Which Man is He?

description:
Friend or Foe?

Keeping his identity secret is now more difficult than ever, but Witchman can't stop yet. Knowing what he must do, he fashions himself a new weapon and gets his chance to test it out when a goblin comes looking for him!

But the battle doesn't end without a price to pay, and Witchman learns the consequences of his failure.
name: Friend or Foe?

description:
The Switching Spell

Rowen's good friend Derrick must come to terms with his new half-goblin form, as well as his new living conditions at the Haunted Tower. But how will Moonie cope with housing a new found member of her sworn enemy, and is there anything Rowen or Rose Wink can do to help the situation?
name: The Switching Spell

description:
Shadows Lurking in the Dark

What lies behind dark crevices and hidden doorways?

Both Rowen and Switch uncover secrets on their own as Rowen continues to deny his friend the opportunity to leave the Haunted Tower. But how safe is a half-goblin to be in the hands of a vengeful demoness? And when will Rowen realize he could use a little help now and then? Goblin activity begins picking up fast as he heads straight into a trap!
name: Shadows Lurking in the Dark

description:
Clouds of Rain and Poison

Chaos ensues as Switch leaves the Haunted Tower and Witchman gets trapped within the walls of the Mayor's Mansion. While one seeks shelter, the other searches for open sky. Neither task is as simple as it seems, especially with the Grayven Guard at your heels. But what makes matters worse is the trail of Wrath breath lingering in the mansion halls. If Sir Michael and his knights can't avoid the red poison, does Witchman have a chance?
name: Clouds of Rain and Poison
